1
00:01:01,540 --> 00:01:05,540
[Producer Zhang Yimou]

2
00:02:30,060 --> 00:02:35,380
[The First Shot]

3
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:38,420
[Episode 25]

4
00:02:39,670 --> 00:02:40,630
Three days ago,

5
00:02:40,910 --> 00:02:42,630
outside a market,

6
00:02:42,630 --> 00:02:44,470
an old man collecting junk died.

7
00:02:44,950 --> 00:02:46,470
There were a lot of people around.

8
00:02:46,910 --> 00:02:48,230
It's said that before he died,

9
00:02:48,590 --> 00:02:50,990
he was very agitated.

10
00:02:51,030 --> 00:02:52,470
How could a junk collector

11
00:02:53,550 --> 00:02:54,670
be doing drugs?

12
00:02:54,670 --> 00:02:56,030
Well, not exactly drugs,

13
00:02:56,190 --> 00:02:58,150
but he did die from meth.

14
00:02:58,270 --> 00:02:59,070
What do you mean?

15
00:02:59,510 --> 00:03:01,510
After meth showed up in Sheng City,

16
00:03:01,790 --> 00:03:03,230
they formed
a Special Investigation Team as well.

17
00:03:03,390 --> 00:03:06,030
They brought a drug expert
from the south to their place,

18
00:03:06,350 --> 00:03:07,630
around your age.

19
00:03:07,760 --> 00:03:08,640
From Yuedong?

20
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:10,280
From Kundu.

21
00:03:12,120 --> 00:03:14,480
Kundu also has a drug problem.
Makes sense.

22
00:03:14,920 --> 00:03:17,240
What makes sense?
They're just copying us.

23
00:03:17,680 --> 00:03:19,000
I brought you to Halan from far away,

24
00:03:19,000 --> 00:03:20,960
thousands of miles.

25
00:03:21,160 --> 00:03:22,640
Now they've done the same.

26
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:23,880
If that's not copying, what is it?

27
00:03:25,920 --> 00:03:27,560
How old are you?

28
00:03:27,920 --> 00:03:29,280
You're too old for this pettiness.

29
00:03:29,640 --> 00:03:30,680
Their expert tested

30
00:03:30,800 --> 00:03:32,920
the residue in the old man's body.

31
00:03:33,400 --> 00:03:35,560
It matched Lucifer.

32
00:03:35,760 --> 00:03:37,480
So Jiang Yingzi

33
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:38,480
transported the drugs

34
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:40,240
three days ago.

35
00:03:40,360 --> 00:03:42,560
Was the old man

36
00:03:43,120 --> 00:03:44,280
using drugs?

37
00:03:44,280 --> 00:03:46,120
The expert says he ingested it.

38
00:03:46,320 --> 00:03:47,240
What?

39
00:03:47,960 --> 00:03:50,320
Ingested meth can be deadly.

40
00:03:51,240 --> 00:03:52,760
But it's in very small amounts.

41
00:03:53,320 --> 00:03:55,320
Plus, he had some health issues.

42
00:03:55,560 --> 00:03:56,560
High blood pressure,

43
00:03:56,760 --> 00:03:57,880
heart problems.

44
00:03:58,320 --> 00:03:59,640
So he didn't make it.

45
00:04:03,600 --> 00:04:05,640
Lucifer is usually sold

46
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:08,080
to high-income buyers

47
00:04:08,360 --> 00:04:10,040
for long-term consumption.

48
00:04:11,120 --> 00:04:12,520
A junk collector

49
00:04:13,920 --> 00:04:15,480
wouldn't normally have access.

50
00:04:15,600 --> 00:04:17,040
So we need to find out

51
00:04:17,680 --> 00:04:18,880
what's happening here.

52
00:04:19,480 --> 00:04:21,960
Did he pick it up by accident,

53
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:24,000
or was it something else?

54
00:04:24,040 --> 00:04:24,840
Let's go.

55
00:04:25,280 --> 00:04:26,640
Let's check his home.

56
00:04:28,100 --> 00:04:32,100
[Lanjiang Province, Sheng City]

57
00:05:21,880 --> 00:05:23,520
Did you test all the food?

58
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,320
Everything edible was tested.

59
00:05:25,640 --> 00:05:26,760
No drugs were found.

60
00:05:27,960 --> 00:05:28,760
Officer Wu.

61
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:29,760
Yes.

62
00:05:31,640 --> 00:05:32,520
Just call me Wu Gang.

63
00:05:32,520 --> 00:05:34,160
I just graduated
from the police academy.

64
00:05:35,000 --> 00:05:37,760
I think we should test

65
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:38,800
his pillows, bedding,

66
00:05:39,200 --> 00:05:40,680
and all the other things.

67
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:41,400
OK.

68
00:05:42,520 --> 00:05:43,320
However...

69
00:05:43,600 --> 00:05:44,400
What's wrong?

70
00:05:44,400 --> 00:05:46,920
The old man probably wasn't an addict.

71
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:48,520
This was his first time.

72
00:05:48,880 --> 00:05:49,960
Still, it is better to test it all,

73
00:05:50,080 --> 00:05:50,960
just in case.

74
00:05:51,640 --> 00:05:52,280
Yeah.

75
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:53,640
Those two are chatting away.

76
00:06:02,280 --> 00:06:04,320
Wu joined yesterday

77
00:06:04,320 --> 00:06:05,000
and started giving us

78
00:06:05,000 --> 00:06:06,720
chemistry lessons.

79
00:06:06,840 --> 00:06:08,120
Gave me a headache.

80
00:06:09,360 --> 00:06:10,160
Yeah, we've all been there.

81
00:06:11,440 --> 00:06:12,440
Alright, let's go out.

82
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:13,520
Sure, get some fresh air.

83
00:06:14,360 --> 00:06:15,160
Let's go.

84
00:06:19,120 --> 00:06:21,840
You and I, we're in the same boat.

85
00:06:22,320 --> 00:06:23,840
If you weren't so plain-looking,

86
00:06:23,880 --> 00:06:25,200
it'd be like looking in a mirror.

87
00:06:25,200 --> 00:06:26,760
Get lost.

88
00:06:28,440 --> 00:06:29,000
You...

89
00:06:29,720 --> 00:06:31,320
You've really come along these 2 years,

90
00:06:31,800 --> 00:06:33,200
looking sharp.

91
00:06:33,720 --> 00:06:34,520
Handsome.

92
00:06:34,840 --> 00:06:36,280
But still, can't find a wife.

93
00:06:36,840 --> 00:06:38,120
Gosh. You talk like you've got one.

94
00:06:38,120 --> 00:06:39,200
Come on.

95
00:06:40,000 --> 00:06:41,440
Remember before school,

96
00:06:41,440 --> 00:06:42,560
you said Cupid was single too.

97
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,880
I am single, so what?

98
00:06:44,400 --> 00:06:45,680
We were all young once.

99
00:06:46,440 --> 00:06:47,720
Didn't see that in you.

100
00:06:48,400 --> 00:06:50,120
Respect me when you talk.

101
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,000
No more joking.

102
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,960
I'm going to ask around next door.

103
00:06:55,040 --> 00:06:56,560
To the left is Grandpa Liu.

104
00:06:56,560 --> 00:06:57,960
Next door is Aunt Wang.

105
00:06:58,240 --> 00:06:59,280
I've asked them all.

106
00:06:59,320 --> 00:07:00,440
The records are in the bureau.

107
00:07:02,360 --> 00:07:03,480
What are you waiting for?

108
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:04,520
Let's go.

109
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,200
Just say what I told you,

110
00:07:08,120 --> 00:07:10,280
and you might have the chance
to get out of here.

111
00:07:12,000 --> 00:07:14,400
I'm heading back.

112
00:07:15,400 --> 00:07:16,600
The trial's next month.

113
00:07:16,960 --> 00:07:18,920
I'll be back next week.

114
00:07:21,240 --> 00:07:22,160
How's Fei?

115
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:28,560
Oh, my bad.

116
00:07:29,000 --> 00:07:29,960
She's fine.

117
00:07:30,200 --> 00:07:32,400
Madam sent her to Sanya.

118
00:07:32,680 --> 00:07:33,960
She just got back yesterday.

119
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:35,920
Oh right,

120
00:07:41,880 --> 00:07:42,920
this is for you.

121
00:07:46,520 --> 00:07:47,760
I can't take this inside.

122
00:07:48,560 --> 00:07:49,480
Take it back.

123
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,320
Have you seen her lately?

124
00:08:02,240 --> 00:08:05,040
She came to my company
before the Mid-Autumn Festival

125
00:08:06,280 --> 00:08:07,560
and asked me to tell you

126
00:08:09,560 --> 00:08:10,600
to take care of yourself.

127
00:08:41,920 --> 00:08:42,920
Lab results showed

128
00:08:42,920 --> 00:08:44,520
that there are

129
00:08:44,520 --> 00:08:46,280
traces of drugs in his system.

130
00:08:46,280 --> 00:08:47,400
[Sheng City Public Security]

131
00:08:47,420 --> 00:08:49,020
How did he get the drugs?

132
00:08:50,260 --> 00:08:51,940
We don't know yet.

133
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:56,860
The old man doesn't seem like
a drug abuser.

134
00:08:57,380 --> 00:08:59,780
Maybe he ingested it by mistake?

135
00:09:00,820 --> 00:09:01,980
Could it be

136
00:09:01,980 --> 00:09:03,700
from another user's leftovers?

137
00:09:03,820 --> 00:09:05,100
It's possible.

138
00:09:05,980 --> 00:09:08,700
Did meth show up before the holiday?

139
00:09:10,540 --> 00:09:12,380
Most appeared

140
00:09:13,740 --> 00:09:14,860
after the Mid-Autumn Festival.

141
00:09:15,020 --> 00:09:16,700
Some nightclubs had it.

142
00:09:17,100 --> 00:09:17,900
We've got eyes

143
00:09:18,140 --> 00:09:20,020
on a couple of pushers,

144
00:09:20,420 --> 00:09:21,700
but we don't want to spook them.

145
00:09:21,740 --> 00:09:22,780
So we're holding off for now.

146
00:09:23,120 --> 00:09:24,400
Yeah, no rush to arrest them.

147
00:09:24,960 --> 00:09:25,840
Let's wait and see.

148
00:09:37,760 --> 00:09:38,560
I'm listening.

149
00:09:43,800 --> 00:09:45,000
Specifically asked to see me?

150
00:09:47,200 --> 00:09:47,880
Okay.

151
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:50,080
I know.

152
00:09:53,560 --> 00:09:55,280
Go back and get me copies

153
00:09:55,280 --> 00:09:56,320
of these photos

154
00:09:56,320 --> 00:09:57,160
and statements.

155
00:09:57,720 --> 00:09:59,120
No problem. Are you heading back?

156
00:09:59,280 --> 00:10:00,640
Halan needs me.

157
00:10:01,160 --> 00:10:02,240
It's mealtime.

158
00:10:02,240 --> 00:10:03,960
Grab something before you go.

159
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:05,200
What to eat?

160
00:10:05,560 --> 00:10:07,240
You guys have got a canteen here?

161
00:10:08,200 --> 00:10:09,040
Of course.

162
00:10:11,400 --> 00:10:12,640
See?

163
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:15,040
They're copying us.

164
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:15,600
Let's go.

165
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,840
Who's copying you?

166
00:10:16,840 --> 00:10:17,600
Bye.

167
00:10:29,640 --> 00:10:30,440
Officer Zheng.

168
00:10:31,600 --> 00:10:33,920
I want to talk to him alone.

169
00:10:34,120 --> 00:10:34,840
Okay.

170
00:10:47,760 --> 00:10:49,280
Why would you want to see me?

171
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:51,960
You've made up your mind?

172
00:10:59,600 --> 00:11:00,400
I...

173
00:11:03,920 --> 00:11:05,400
I need a favor.

174
00:11:07,160 --> 00:11:08,560
Sure, go ahead.

175
00:11:11,000 --> 00:11:11,880
Talk straight,

176
00:11:12,200 --> 00:11:13,320
just as I do.

177
00:11:18,920 --> 00:11:20,920
Can you check on my daughter?

178
00:11:22,480 --> 00:11:23,760
Why me?

179
00:11:25,400 --> 00:11:26,440
Shouldn't you

180
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:28,600
ask your lawyer to do that?

181
00:11:29,160 --> 00:11:30,440
He lied to me.

182
00:11:30,880 --> 00:11:31,960
I don't trust him.

183
00:11:34,040 --> 00:11:35,320
My daughter's name is Jin Fei.

184
00:11:36,120 --> 00:11:36,960
She's young

185
00:11:38,400 --> 00:11:39,320
and naive,

186
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:40,760
easy to be taken advantage of.

187
00:11:41,640 --> 00:11:43,440
My eyelids keep twitching.

188
00:11:43,480 --> 00:11:44,800
I'm worried something's happened to her.

189
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:47,560
Can you...?

190
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:56,200
Tell me everything you know,

191
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:58,680
about her friends,

192
00:11:58,960 --> 00:12:00,120
hobbies,

193
00:12:00,560 --> 00:12:01,800
and places she likes to go.

194
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:03,240
As much as you can.

195
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:48,520
Jin Fei.

196
00:12:48,520 --> 00:12:49,480
Move fast.

197
00:12:49,480 --> 00:12:49,840
Go.

198
00:12:49,840 --> 00:12:50,600
Come on, Jin Fei!

199
00:12:50,840 --> 00:12:51,880
- Hurry up!
- Faster.

200
00:12:52,000 --> 00:12:53,160
Quick.

201
00:13:15,040 --> 00:13:15,720
Look,

202
00:13:16,040 --> 00:13:18,240
I saw a really handsome guy

203
00:13:18,640 --> 00:13:19,640
over there earlier.

204
00:13:19,920 --> 00:13:21,200
In a white T-shirt.

205
00:13:22,840 --> 00:13:23,840
He went that way.

206
00:13:23,840 --> 00:13:24,480
Which one?

207
00:13:25,080 --> 00:13:26,040
So handsome.

208
00:13:26,200 --> 00:13:27,240
Handsome, right?

209
00:13:27,280 --> 00:13:28,200
I saw him too.

210
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,160
I'll make a phone call.

211
00:14:08,600 --> 00:14:10,200
Special Task Force, Xin Tiegang.

212
00:14:10,360 --> 00:14:11,920
Uncle, ask Bei to answer the phone.

213
00:14:12,120 --> 00:14:12,920
One second.

214
00:14:13,240 --> 00:14:14,040
Bei.

215
00:14:15,080 --> 00:14:15,880
Bei.

216
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:17,640
Come, your call.

217
00:14:17,760 --> 00:14:18,560
Who is it?

218
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:20,320
Seems to be Yao.

219
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:21,760
Hello?

220
00:14:22,440 --> 00:14:24,200
Something's off with Jin Fei.

221
00:14:24,760 --> 00:14:26,320
At first,

222
00:14:26,320 --> 00:14:27,600
I thought she was just in a bad mood,

223
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,240
acting differently from others.

224
00:14:29,480 --> 00:14:31,520
Then I took a closer look.

225
00:14:31,520 --> 00:14:32,920
She seems like,

226
00:14:35,360 --> 00:14:37,280
according to what Ran taught,

227
00:14:37,320 --> 00:14:38,720
like she's using drugs.

228
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,160
Jin Fei, using drugs?

229
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,240
I think so.

230
00:14:42,440 --> 00:14:44,200
When we arrested Erjin before,

231
00:14:44,200 --> 00:14:45,400
I talked to her.

232
00:14:45,480 --> 00:14:46,600
She wasn't like this.

233
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,520
She was normal.

234
00:14:48,680 --> 00:14:50,600
I suspect she tried drugs recently.

235
00:14:52,400 --> 00:14:53,520
Got it.

236
00:15:35,720 --> 00:15:37,040
Hai.

237
00:15:45,240 --> 00:15:46,600
Money.

238
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:50,680
Get lost.

239
00:17:29,760 --> 00:17:31,160
Great, you're still here.

240
00:17:32,080 --> 00:17:33,400
Why are you here so late?

241
00:17:34,240 --> 00:17:35,200
Take a look at this.

242
00:17:38,200 --> 00:17:39,320
Songlin Police Station.

243
00:17:40,160 --> 00:17:42,040
Jin Fei was drinking

244
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:44,280
near Wanhuang Hotel
during the Mid-Autumn Festival.

245
00:17:44,560 --> 00:17:45,520
Later that night,

246
00:17:45,600 --> 00:17:47,000
someone saw her at the police station.

247
00:17:56,260 --> 00:18:01,700
[Caller: Jin Fei,
report: Lin Jiang raped me]

248
00:18:11,340 --> 00:18:14,420
[Family members of the complainant:
Jiang Yingzi, Lin Jiang]

249
00:18:19,060 --> 00:18:23,220
[Action taken: Domestic dispute,
case dropped]

250
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:28,320
That rascal.

251
00:18:28,320 --> 00:18:29,800
I'll blow him up.

252
00:18:29,920 --> 00:18:32,720
Let me out. I'll kill him.

253
00:18:33,160 --> 00:18:33,840
Calm down!

254
00:18:35,640 --> 00:18:36,240
Relax.

255
00:18:38,080 --> 00:18:38,880
Liu.

256
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:40,920
Alright, it's okay now.

257
00:18:50,760 --> 00:18:51,640
Officer,

258
00:18:52,480 --> 00:18:54,760
can I get out for a day?

259
00:18:55,080 --> 00:18:55,960
Just one day.

260
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:57,000
Half a day even.

261
00:18:57,000 --> 00:18:59,160
I promise I'll come back
after I'm done. I won't run.

262
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:01,080
Please.

263
00:19:01,520 --> 00:19:02,680
Do you think it's possible?

264
00:19:02,960 --> 00:19:03,800
I'm begging you.

265
00:19:05,200 --> 00:19:06,240
I'm begging you.

266
00:19:06,240 --> 00:19:08,200
I just have this one daughter.

267
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,440
Just one.

268
00:19:11,920 --> 00:19:14,880
I've spoiled her since she was little,

269
00:19:14,880 --> 00:19:17,840
and I never let her suffer.

270
00:19:19,200 --> 00:19:21,560
I'm a thug; I deserve this.

271
00:19:21,560 --> 00:19:23,240
But she isn't.

272
00:19:23,520 --> 00:19:26,120
How dare that rascal do this to her?

273
00:19:26,120 --> 00:19:28,080
How dare he?

274
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,920
If I were out,

275
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:36,760
who'd dare touch my daughter?

276
00:19:37,400 --> 00:19:39,000
Who?

277
00:19:39,080 --> 00:19:40,000
But you're not out.

278
00:19:42,880 --> 00:19:44,240
You committed a crime,

279
00:19:45,120 --> 00:19:46,480
a serious one.

280
00:19:47,360 --> 00:19:48,840
You're locked up.

281
00:19:49,280 --> 00:19:50,480
How can you protect her?

282
00:20:00,600 --> 00:20:02,320
It's all my fault.

283
00:20:03,090 --> 00:20:05,050
I failed Fei.

284
00:20:07,210 --> 00:20:08,850
I'm the one to blame.

285
00:20:11,850 --> 00:20:15,130
I've been hanging on for what?

286
00:20:20,930 --> 00:20:22,250
I've been meaning to ask you the same.

287
00:20:22,890 --> 00:20:24,010
For what?

288
00:20:25,370 --> 00:20:27,730
You've been here for so long,

289
00:20:27,730 --> 00:20:29,330
and never said a word.

290
00:20:29,730 --> 00:20:31,170
Qin Yi is dead.

291
00:20:31,530 --> 00:20:33,610
There's no point protecting him.

292
00:20:35,410 --> 00:20:36,770
